ActCustoms Tariff
SubjectOrder Repealing the Certain Goods Remission Order (COVID-19)
PrecisOrder REPEALING THE CERTAIN GOODS REMISSION ORDER (COVID-19) in order to reinstate (1) applicable customs duties on imports of specified medical supplies, including personal protective equipment (PPE), that were waived on a temporary and emergency basis in response to the COVID-19 pandemic; and (2) most-favoured nation tariffs on specified goods, including PPE, to the rates in effect immediately before the Certain Goods Remission Order (COVID-19) took effect.
